cs.CR, cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SI

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on privacy-preserving speech transcription and proposes a system to protect sensitive acoustic and textual information.
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper deals with speech transcription and the performance of ASR systems.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is another possible category as the paper discusses the transcription of speech into text.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper mentions the use of machine learning in ASR systems.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the privacy risks associated with speech data.
